holding over this year.

09:55.526 --> 09:57.935
Mm-hmm.

09:57.935 --> 10:00.839
Oh, yes. I know
a couple of these reprobates.

10:00.839 --> 10:05.635
Let's be a little more elastic
in our assessment, shall we?

10:05.635 --> 10:08.275
It's hard enough for them to be
away from home on the holidays.

10:08.275 --> 10:10.882
Latitude is the last thing
these boys need.

10:12.314 --> 10:16.723
Paul, at your core,
you're an excellent teacher,

10:16.723 --> 10:19.792
but your approach to the
students is rather traditional.

10:19.792 --> 10:21.827
This school was founded in 1797.

10:21.827 --> 10:24.390
I thought tradition
was our stock in trade.

10:24.390 --> 10:26.194
- Then let's call it hidebound.
- Ah.

10:26.194 --> 10:28.702
You know, unwavering,
resistant to...

10:28.702 --> 10:31.133
Yes, yes, yes, I know
what "hidebound" means.

10:31.133 --> 10:33.333
Uh, I get it.

10:33.333 --> 10:36.072
You're still angry
that I failed Jordan Osgood.

10:36.072 --> 10:38.712
Senator Osgood was very upset

10:38.712 --> 10:41.539
when Princeton rescinded
Jordan's acceptance, yes.

10:41.539 --> 10:43.915
And I've continued to
have to deal with the fallout.

10:43.915 --> 10:47.347
Hardy, are we really supposed
to let these boys just skate by

10:47.347 --> 10:49.723
as long as Daddy builds
a new gymnasium?

10:49.723 --> 10:51.857
Of course not.
That's not who we are.

10:51.857 --> 10:54.222
But we can't be ignorant
to politics.

10:54.222 --> 10:57.093
That boy is too dumb
to pour piss out of a boot.

10:57.093 --> 10:59.161
A genuine troglodyte.

10:59.161 --> 11:01.229
Jesus Christ, Paul.

11:01.229 --> 11:04.001
He was a legacy and the son
of one of our biggest donors.

11:04.001 --> 11:05.838
Ever think his dad
might be expecting

11:05.838 --> 11:07.840
a little consideration
for his dollar?

11:07.840 --> 11:11.371
And he got it-- a first-class
education for his son.

11:11.371 --> 11:13.076
Oh, come on, Hardy.

11:13.076 --> 11:17.278
As Dr. Greene used to say,
"Our one true purpose

11:17.278 --> 11:19.379
is to produce young men
of good character."

11:19.379 --> 11:21.513
I don't care what
Dr. Greene used to say.

11:21.513 --> 11:23.350
"And we cannot sacrifice
our integrity

11:23.350 --> 11:25.253
on the altar
of their entitlement."

11:25.253 --> 11:29.290
I'm just trying to instill
basic academic discipline.

11:29.290 --> 11:31.798
That's my job. Isn't it yours?

11:31.798 --> 11:33.558
It was.

11:33.558 --> 11:35.593
Until I became headmaster

11:35.593 --> 11:38.629
and saw that it's not so simple
to keep the damn school afloat.

11:38.629 --> 11:42.908
I begged you, begged you
to give the kid a C minus.

11:42.908 --> 11:44.371
(chuckles):
No.

11:44.371 --> 11:45.944
There are instructors here
who will do that.

11:45.944 --> 11:48.012
I am not one of them.

11:52.315 --> 11:55.745
Here's the manual
and a full set of keys.

11:55.745 --> 11:57.890
Everything you need to know
is in there.

11:57.890 --> 12:00.057
Your only task is to ensure

12:00.057 --> 12:02.554
the boys' absolute safety
and good condition.

12:02.554 --> 12:06.965
And at least pretend to be
a human being.

12:06.965 --> 12:08.901
Please.

12:08.901 --> 12:10.936
It's Christmas.

12:10.936 --> 12:12.938
<i>(bells jingling)</i>

12:12.938 --> 12:15.600
♪ ♪

12:15.600 --> 12:18.009
